{
  "info": {
    "name": "Inksight API",
    "description": "AI-powered visual assistant API for image upload and conversational chat with real-time streaming.\n\n## Setup\n\n1. Import this collection into Postman (no environment file needed)\n2. Start the server: `cp .env.example .env && docker compose up --build -d --wait`\n3. All URLs default to `http://localhost:3000` via the `base_url` collection variable\n\n## Running the Collection\n\nUse the **Collection Runner** to execute all requests in order. The Upload Image request auto-captures `imageId` for all subsequent requests.\n\n1. **Upload Image** - uploads a test image and captures `imageId`\n2. **Chat (Non-Streaming)** - sends a message about the uploaded image\n3. **Chat (Streaming SSE)** - sends a message and receives streaming response\n4. **Get Chat History** - retrieves conversation history for the image\n5. **List Images (Gallery)** - lists all uploaded images with pagination\n6. **Serve Image File** - downloads the original image file\n7. **Delete Image** - deletes the image and all associated data\n8. **Health Check** - verifies system health\n\n## Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Set By |\n|----------|-------------|--------|\n| `base_url` | Server base URL (default: `http://localhost:3000`) | Collection variable |\n| `imageId` | UUID of the uploaded image | Upload request (auto-captured) |\n\n## Error Format\n\nAll errors return a consistent JSON shape:\n```json\n{\n  \"statusCode\": 400,\n  \"error\": \"Bad Request\",\n  \"code\": \"ERROR_CODE\",\n  \"message\": \"Description\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"ISO 8601\",\n  \"path\": \"/api/...\",\n  \"requestId\": \"UUID\"\n}\n```",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Server base URL. Change this if running on a different port."
    },
    {
      "key": "imageId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-captured from the Upload Image request. No need to set manually."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Upload Image",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 201 Created', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has correct structure', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('filename');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('mimeType');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('size');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('analysis');",
              "    pm.expect(json.id).to.match(/^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-4[0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/i);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Capture imageId for subsequent requests', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('imageId', json.id);",
              "    console.log('Captured imageId:', json.id);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has X-Request-Id header', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.header('X-Request-Id');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [],
        "body": {
          "mode": "formdata",
          "formdata": [
            {
              "key": "image",
              "type": "file",
              "src": "",
              "description": "Image file to upload (PNG, JPEG, or GIF \u2014 max 16 MB). Select a file before sending."
            }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/upload",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "upload"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Upload an image for AI analysis.\n\n**File Requirements:**\n- Accepted types: `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.gif`\n- Maximum size: 16 MB\n- Form field name: `image`\n\nThe server validates file extension, size, and magic bytes (file content signature). Files are stored with a UUID filename for security \u2014 the original filename is preserved in metadata only.\n\n**Rate Limit:** 10 requests per minute\n\n**Response:** Returns image metadata with an initial AI vision analysis."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Chat (Non-Streaming)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200 OK', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response is OpenAI Chat Completion format', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id');",
              "    pm.expect(json.object).to.equal('chat.completion');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('model');",
              "    pm.expect(json.choices).to.be.an('array').with.length(1);",
              "    pm.expect(json.choices[0].message.role).to.equal('assistant');",
              "    pm.expect(json.choices[0].message.content).to.be.a('string');",
              "    pm.expect(json.choices[0].finish_reason).to.equal('stop');",
              "    pm.expect(json.usage).to.have.all.keys('prompt_tokens', 'completion_tokens', 'total_tokens');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has X-Request-Id header', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.header('X-Request-Id');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"message\": \"What objects can you identify in this image?\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/chat/{{imageId}}",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "chat",
            "{{imageId}}"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Send a chat message about the uploaded image and receive a complete AI response.\n\nThe conversation history is automatically included as context for the AI. Both the user message and the assistant response are persisted to the conversation history.\n\n**Rate Limit:** 30 requests per minute\n\n**Response:** OpenAI-compatible Chat Completion object with the assistant's analysis."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Chat (Streaming SSE)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200 OK', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Content-Type is text/event-stream', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('text/event-stream');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response contains SSE data lines', function () {",
              "    const body = pm.response.text();",
              "    pm.expect(body).to.include('data: ');",
              "    pm.expect(body).to.include('data: [DONE]');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Stream chunks are valid JSON', function () {",
              "    const body = pm.response.text();",
              "    const lines = body.split('\\n').map(l => l.trim()).filter(l => l.startsWith('data: ') && l !== 'data: [DONE]');",
              "    lines.forEach(function(line) {",
              "        const json = JSON.parse(line.substring(6));",
              "        pm.expect(json.object).to.equal('chat.completion.chunk');",
              "        pm.expect(json.choices).to.be.an('array');",
              "    });",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"message\": \"Describe the colors and lighting in this image.\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/chat-stream/{{imageId}}",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "chat-stream",
            "{{imageId}}"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Send a chat message and receive a streaming response via Server-Sent Events (SSE).\n\nThe response is a stream of `data:` lines, each containing a JSON chunk in OpenAI streaming format. The stream ends with `data: [DONE]`.\n\n**Stream Format:**\n```\ndata: {\"id\":\"chatcmpl-...\",\"object\":\"chat.completion.chunk\",\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"role\":\"assistant\"},\"finish_reason\":null}]}\n\ndata: {\"id\":\"chatcmpl-...\",\"object\":\"chat.completion.chunk\",\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"content\":\"word\"},\"finish_reason\":null}]}\n\ndata: [DONE]\n```\n\n**Rate Limit:** 30 requests/minute + max 5 concurrent SSE connections per IP\n\n**Timeout:** 30 seconds (configurable, max 120s)"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Get Chat History",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200 OK', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has correct pagination structure', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('imageId');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('messages').that.is.an('array');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('totalMessages');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('page');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('pageSize');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('totalPages');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Messages have correct structure', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    if (json.messages.length > 0) {",
              "        const msg = json.messages[0];",
              "        pm.expect(msg).to.have.all.keys('id', 'role', 'content', 'timestamp');",
              "        pm.expect(['user', 'assistant']).to.include(msg.role);",
              "    }",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('History contains messages from previous requests', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json.totalMessages).to.be.greaterThan(0);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/chat/{{imageId}}/history?page=1&limit=20",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "chat",
            "{{imageId}}",
            "history"
          ],
          "query": [
            {
              "key": "page",
              "value": "1",
              "description": "Page number (1-indexed, default: 1)"
            },
            {
              "key": "limit",
              "value": "20",
              "description": "Items per page (1-50, default: 20)"
            }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Retrieve the paginated conversation history for an image. Messages are ordered by creation time (ascending).\n\nThe image must exist \u2014 returns 404 otherwise.\n\nEach message includes: `id`, `role` (user/assistant), `content`, and `timestamp`."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "List Images (Gallery)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200 OK', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has correct pagination structure', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('images').that.is.an('array');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('total');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('page');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('pageSize');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('totalPages');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Gallery contains the uploaded image', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    const imageId = pm.collectionVariables.get('imageId');",
              "    const found = json.images.find(img => img.id === imageId);",
              "    pm.expect(found).to.not.be.undefined;",
              "    pm.expect(found).to.have.all.keys('id', 'originalFilename', 'mimeType', 'size', 'messageCount', 'createdAt');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Image has message count > 0 from chat requests', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    const imageId = pm.collectionVariables.get('imageId');",
              "    const found = json.images.find(img => img.id === imageId);",
              "    if (found) {",
              "        pm.expect(found.messageCount).to.be.greaterThan(0);",
              "    }",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/images?page=1&limit=20",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "images"
          ],
          "query": [
            {
              "key": "page",
              "value": "1",
              "description": "Page number (1-indexed, default: 1)"
            },
            {
              "key": "limit",
              "value": "20",
              "description": "Items per page (1-50, default: 20)"
            }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Returns a paginated list of all uploaded images, ordered by creation date (newest first).\n\nEach entry includes image metadata and a count of associated chat messages. No file content or conversation history is returned \u2014 use the specific endpoints for those."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Serve Image File",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200 OK', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Content-Type is an image type', function () {",
              "    const ct = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type');",
              "    pm.expect(ct).to.match(/^image\\/(png|jpeg|gif)/);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Has Cache-Control header', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Cache-Control')).to.include('max-age=31536000');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Has Content-Disposition header', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.header('Content-Disposition');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/images/{{imageId}}/file",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "images",
            "{{imageId}}",
            "file"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Streams the original image file from disk.\n\n**Response Headers:**\n- `Content-Type` \u2014 Set from the database record (not guessed from extension)\n- `Content-Disposition: inline; filename=\"original_name.ext\"` \u2014 URL-encoded original filename\n- `Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable` \u2014 1 year cache (files are immutable by UUID)"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Delete Image",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 204 No Content', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(204);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response body is empty', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.be.empty;",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "DELETE",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/images/{{imageId}}",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "images",
            "{{imageId}}"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Permanently deletes an image, its file on disk, and all associated chat messages (cascade delete).\n\nInvalidates related caches. Returns 204 with no body on success.\n\nSubsequent requests to this imageId will return 404."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Health Check",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status code is 200 OK', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status is healthy', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json.status).to.equal('healthy');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Database is connected', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json.checks.database).to.equal('connected');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has correct structure', function () {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('timestamp');",
              "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('checks');",
              "    pm.expect(json.checks).to.have.property('database');",
              "    pm.expect(json.checks).to.have.property('uptime');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health",
          "host": [
            "{{base_url}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "health"
          ]
        },
        "description": "Performs an active database connectivity check via `SELECT 1` and returns system status.\n\n**Exempt from rate limiting.**\n\nReturns `200` with `status: \"healthy\"` when the database is reachable, or `503` with `status: \"degraded\"` when the database is unreachable."
      },
      "response": []
    }
  ]
}
